Structure and Essay Questions (1990)
The two blocks in the figure A and B has the masses mi and m2 respectively. There are connected by a light string and an upward force of F N is applied vertically as shown in the figure.
(i) Mark the forces acting on A, B and the string in separate diagrams. (ii) If m1= 2 kg, m2=8 kg and F=110 N find the acceleration of the system. (iii) Find the tension of the rope at the end that has been connected to A and at the end that has been connected to B.
(iv) If the string is replaced by a heavy string with mass 1 kg repeat the part (ii) and (iii). And find the tension of the rope at the mid-point.
